AC.name: Quarantine agency
AC.desc: Agency responsible for the administration of statutory disease controls on the movement of people, animals and plants.

CA.name: Carrier
CA.desc: Party undertaking or arranging transport of goods between named points.

CU.name: Customs
CU.desc: 'Customs' means the Government Service which is responsible for the administration of Customs law and the collection of duties and taxes and which also has the responsibility for the application of other laws and regulations relating to the importation, exportation, movement or storage of goods.

SH.name: Shipper
SH.desc: Party which, by contract with a carrier, consigns or sends goods with the carrier, or has them conveyed by him.

TO.name: Terminal operator
TO.desc: Party which handles the loading and unloading of marine vessels.
